Lower centre (left to right): faded human figure face on; infilled camel facing left, cow facing right with u-shaped horns; cow facing right; graffiti in Arab script (awaiting translation). description.value: Digital photograph (colour); view of painted rock art on a sandstone cave wall, showing the painted, infilled figures of two human figures and six unidentified shapes.  The human figures are of commensurate size and infilled in brown. The other human figure lies above this, turned to the side and facing down with the head to the right and body curving down at the waist, with straight, slightly splayed legs. description.value:
Digital photograph (colour); detail of engraved rock art on a rock face showing five human figures and three cupules. The panel is organized around five human figures of different sizes upright facing left, with the arm to the right outstretched and the hand to the right infilled with pecking. Some of them have the arm to the left bent, holding a stick over the shoulder and horizontal, unidentified shapes across the neck. The buttocks and thighs of the figures are abnormally wide (steatopygia?). All figures are infilled with pecked geometric patterns as straight and wavy lines, squares, meanders (garments? tattoos?). At the centre of the panel there are six polished oval cupules. Niola Doa, Chad.
Scanned

description.value:
Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on a rock face showing eight human figures and an unidentified shape. The panel is organized around seven outlined, pecked women of different sizes. The seven to the left are upright facing left, while the one to the rightmost is facing front.Some of the figures have the arm to the right outstretched down and the arm to the right bent up, some with both arms outstretched down. The figures have buttocks and thighs abnormally wide (steatopygia?) and are total or partially infilled with pecked geometric patterns as straight and wavy lines, squares or meanders (garments? tattoos?). The third woman from the right holds a stick over the shoulder. The Ennedi Plateau cliffs can be seen in the background. The Ennedi Plateau cliffs can be seen in the background. A 20 cm photo scale has been fitted at the bottom of the tableau. Niola Doa, Chad.

description.value:
Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on a rock face showing three human figures. To the centre there are two outlined (pecked) women upright facing left, with the arm to the right outstretched, and the arms to the left bent up. The woman to the left holds a stick over the shoulder, with three lines (leather strips) hanging from the side, and several lines coming out of the head (headdress?). The woman to the right wears a skirt. The figures have buttocks and thighs abnormally wide (steatopygia?). The figures are infilled with pecked geometric patterns as straight and wavy lines, squares and meanders representing (garments? tattoos?). At the lower centre there is an outlined, pecked human figure upright facing left with the arm to the right outstretched down and the arm to the right holding a stick. Two lines (feathers?) come out of the head. Niola Doa, Chad.
